label: A12B2C_cF60_196_h_ac_b-001
title: Cu$_{2}$Fe[CN]$_{6}$ Structure
comments:
The sites we have labeled as carbon are actually a 50-50 mixture of carbon and nitrogen. 
 This structure is taken from (Villars, 2013), repeated in \href{https://materials.springer.com/isp/crystallographic/docs/sd_1902947}{(Villars, 2023)}. Our print versions of (Rigamonti, 1937) gives a structure consistent with the \href{current_web_home_dir/A6B2C_cF36_225_e_c_a-001}{K$_{2}$PtCl$_{6}$ ($J1_{1}$)} prototype.
